            <div>
                <head>General Structure of SSK scenarios and steps</head>
                <p>The SSK offers complete frameworks to researchers needing standardized methods
                    and resources to carry out their project, in Arts and Humanities and Heritage
                    science. </p>
                <p>This guidance takes the form of step by step research scenarios where the use of
                    standards is clearly identified. Theses scenarios are divided into different
                    steps, implying specific tasks. Each step contains a set of bibliographical
                    resources. </p>
                <p> A scenario is a list of events (<gi>listEvents</gi>), each scenario step is an
                    event (<gi>event</gi>).</p>
                <p>The <gi>event</gi> is the core element of the SSK scenario. It is usable in two
                    different contexts: <list>
                        <item>A full description of the scenario step, with all the bibliographical
                            references included. These events are stored in single files.</item>
                        <item>In a given scenario, event elements are used as pointers to link to
                            full event elements stored in external files</item>
                    </list></p>
                <p>Events are stored in external files, allowing them to be used in different
                    scenarios The resources consists of Bibliographical references. They are of two
                    types : “general resources” and “project specific”. These elements can be
                    repeated (one per "project"). At each level, the elements are enriched with
                    keywords that can be <gi>term</gi> or XML attributes </p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <head>Scenarios</head>
                <p>The structure of the Scenario header is as follows:</p>

                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <TEI type="scenario">
                        <fileDesc>
                            <titleStmt>

                                <title><!-- Title of the tei document, not title of the scenario --></title>
                                <author>
                                    <persName>...</persName>
                                    <affiliation>...</affiliation>
                                </author>
                            </titleStmt>
                            <publicationStmt>
                                <authority>Parthenos ...</authority>
                                <availability>
                                    <licence target="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">
                                        <p>The Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 Unported (CC BY 4.0)
                                            Licence applies to this document.</p>
                                    </licence>
                                </availability>
                            </publicationStmt>
                            <sourceDesc>
                                <p>Created from scratch</p>
                            </sourceDesc>
                        </fileDesc>
                        <revisionDesc>
                            <change>
                                <!-- Only for major changes: addition of an author, of a step, etc. -->
                            </change>
                        </revisionDesc>
                    </TEI>
                </egXML>
                <p>The scenario header includes the following data elements:</p>
                <list type="unordered">
                    <item>the title of the document (which is not the title of the scenario</item>
                    <item>the authors of the scenarios</item>
                    <item>the majors modifications</item>
                </list>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Steps</head>
                <p>The structure of the step header is as follows:</p>
