            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Main elements used in our SSK TEI</head>
                <list>
                    <item><gi>event</gi></item>
                    <item><gi>head</gi></item>
                    <item><gi>term</gi></item>
                    <item><gi>label</gi></item>
                    <item><gi>desc</gi></item>
                    <item><gi>listRef</gi></item>
                </list>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Major features of the SSK customization</head>
                <list>
                    <item/>
                    <item>All the <gi>TEI</gi> elements must be typed, either with the values
                        "scenario" or "step"</item>
                    <item>The attribute <att>mode</att> is used to refine the results when a step is
                        used in more than one scenario</item>
                    <item><att>xml:lang</att> in mandatory for:<list>
                            <item><gi>label</gi></item>
                            <item><gi>desc</gi></item>
                            <item><gi>term</gi></item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>All elements that use <att>mode</att> are member or the class
                        att.combinable.</item>
                    <item><gi>figure</gi> is used in <gi>head</gi>, especially the <gi>head</gi>
                        present in the <gi>div</gi> presenting the scenario, to provide an image for
                        the scenario</item>
                </list>
            </div>

